One of the main benefits is that queries are written with association to the object/s and it's properties, 
whereas with the sql queries are written with the association of tables and it's columns.
With Symbiotic Query, after the mapping attributes are added, you don't have to think about the schema or the columns, just the objects.

Also if the developer uses the Symbiotic Query api properly, many parts of the query are compiler checked, so if you change an objects name or property the compiler will show an error.

Database abstraction of queries.
Provides the developer the ability to write queries in code.
Provides compiler checked queries.
More secure as all queries are parameterized.
Queries are not database vendor dependent.
summary: The main purpose of this library is to provide a true abstraction from the database while allowing the developer to write database agnostic queries referencing the objects instead of the database.

Chocolatey is brought to you by the work and inspiration of the community, the work and thankless nights of the Chocolatey Team (https://github.com/orgs/chocolatey/people), and Rob heading up the direction.

This is the core package which allows Chocolatey to be embedded in your application.

description:
BundleTransformer.SassAndScss contains translator-adapter `SassAndScssTranslator`. This adapter makes translation of Sass- and SCSS-code to CSS-code by using the LibSass Host for .NET (http://github.com/Taritsyn/LibSassHost) version 1.0.2 (supports libSass version 3.4.3). Also contains debugging HTTP-handler `SassAndScssAssetHandler`, which is responsible for text output of translated Sass- or SCSS-asset.

This package does not contain the native implementations of libSass for Windows. Therefore, you need to choose and install the most appropriate package(s) for your platform. The following packages are available:

 * LibSassHost.Native.win-x86
 * LibSassHost.Native.win-x64

For correct working of the LibSass Host requires `msvcp140.dll` assembly from the Visual C++ Redistributable for Visual Studio 2015.
summary: BundleTransformer.SassAndScss contains translator-adapter `SassAndScssTranslator`. This adapter makes translation of Sass- and SCSS-code to CSS-code by using the LibSass Host for .NET version 1.0.2 (supports libSass version 3.4.3). Also contains debugging HTTP-handler `SassAndScssAssetHandler`, which is responsible for text output of translated Sass- or SCSS-asset.

description:
BundleTransformer.Autoprefixer contains one postprocessor-adapter for postprocessing of CSS-code - `AutoprefixCssPostProcessor`. `AutoprefixCssPostProcessor` is based on the Andrey Sitnik's Autoprefixer (http://github.com/postcss/autoprefixer) version 6.7.7.1.

As a JS-engine is used the JavaScript Engine Switcher library (http://github.com/Taritsyn/JavaScriptEngineSwitcher). For correct working of this module is recommended to install the following NuGet packages: JavaScriptEngineSwitcher.Msie, JavaScriptEngineSwitcher.V8 or JavaScriptEngineSwitcher.ChakraCore.
